-- Standard Chartered Banker Gets $16 Million, Sunday Times Says
-- B y   P a t r i c i a   K u o
-- 2012-03-18T09:24:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-18/standard-chartered-banker-gets-16-million-sunday-times-says.html
Mike Rees , head of  Standard
Chartered Plc’s (STAN)  investment bank, was paid 10 million pounds ($16
million) in salary and bonus after profit at his wholesale
banking division reached a record last year, the Sunday Times
reported.  Profit at the unit increased to $5.2 billion from $4.8
billion in 2011 and now accounts for 77 percent of Standard
Chartered’s earnings, according to the newspaper.  The payout is set to be confirmed in the London-based
bank’s annual report on Friday, the newspaper said. Rees
received $14 million in salary and bonus in 2010, according to
the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
